00:06:15.117 --> 00:06:27.189
When we upload the image the first thing it does is it randomly puts a hundred points on that image and then after I label what's underneath each of those 100 points it gives you the idea of percent coverage,

00:06:27.189 --> 00:06:32.301
so what percentage of this particular part of the reef is living coral, what percentage is algae,

00:06:32.301 --> 00:06:34.622
and what percentage is sand or dead coral.

00:06:34.622 --> 00:06:37.476
And that gives us an indication of how healthy the reef is.

00:06:37.476 --> 00:06:44.072
